Super SpriteMan
Version 0.7.1 (August 2010) 

You are allowed to do whatever you want with this program as long as you
include the present file and include a copy of the work in its original
form.

Game requirements : 
SDL 1.2 (http://www.libsdl.org)

Game controls :
Press F at the splash screen to activate full screen mode

Left and right cursor keys - walking & running
Up cursor key - jump
Down cursor key - fall trough platform
Space key - kick, go through door, pickup/throw bowling ball
Escape key - quit

Developer mode (activated by default) controls ("cheats") :
A key - Warp to level 2
Q key - quit game
R key - reset game
T key - rapidly move to the left
Y key - rapidly move to the right
U key - hold player at vertical coordinate 0
J key - force infinite jump
F key - set test warp point to current coordinates
G key - do test warp
K key - kill player
V key - force camera down
F1 key - Show FPS
F2 key - Show version

Level files (Windows and Unix) :
This new version of Super SpriteMan comes with new levels,
which you can find in the "levels" directory.
To run a level file, copy it to the "bin" directory, go to
the "bin" directory, and use a command line such as
"./ssm SomeMap.ssm" or "ssm SomeMap.ssm" (Windows)


